1
00:00:00,070 --> 00:00:08,250
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

2
00:00:08,250 --> 00:00:10,750
We meet again, Ms. Yi Yeong.

3
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:13,680
It's been a while, right?

4
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:19,360
Ahjussi, you chased me like this last year, didn't you?

5
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:25,930
The day Kim Ian died, you were the one who came after me. Right?

6
00:00:27,630 --> 00:00:31,480
Episode 21

7
00:00:33,090 --> 00:00:40,050
Night of Encouragement

8
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:06,840
You finally remember me.

9
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:10,810
It's been tough keeping it from you all this time.

10
00:01:11,540 --> 00:01:13,650
Why did you come to my aunt's flower shop?

11
00:01:13,650 --> 00:01:15,590
What do you want to do to her?

12
00:01:15,590 --> 00:01:20,110
Look, don't get worked up.

13
00:01:20,110 --> 00:01:24,990
As soon as I find my things, I will quietly disappear.

14
00:01:24,990 --> 00:01:29,660
As long as you don't make me mad, I won't do anything.

15
00:01:31,770 --> 00:01:34,650
As long as you don't make me mad.

16
00:01:42,690 --> 00:01:45,740
What is it you are looking for?

17
00:01:45,740 --> 00:01:48,670
You told me while we were in the warehouse that you were looking for something.

18
00:01:48,670 --> 00:01:50,620
I will find it.

19
00:01:50,620 --> 00:01:52,610
Tell me what it is.

20
00:01:52,610 --> 00:01:59,200
And... don't come see my family again. Please.

21
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:02,130
You're going to find it for me?

22
00:02:04,370 --> 00:02:06,320
I'll find it for you. I'm serious.

23
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:12,580
In exchange, tell me what happened that day.

24
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:15,400
You know what happened, don't you?

25
00:02:16,410 --> 00:02:21,360
One that day a year ago, what happened?

26
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:05,500
What are you doing?

27
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:10,760
Since when have you known CEO Jang? Why did you come with him?

28
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:15,140
After making a scene and crying in front of you, I went to see him.

29
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:18,120
I have wasted many opportunities because of you.

30
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,980
Did you tell Jang Yun about that night?

31
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:23,060
Just what were you thinking, telling him about that?

32
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:25,690
I told him truthfully what I saw.

33
00:03:25,690 --> 00:03:27,590
You did follow Kim Ian's car that night.

34
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:30,240
I saw it all.

35
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,910
I told you, I went home. You misunderstood, that is all.

36
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:34,760
Please don't lie.

37
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:37,890
You became interested in Hong Yi Yeong after that night.

38
00:03:37,890 --> 00:03:41,120
Before that, you only knew her name.

39
00:03:41,830 --> 00:03:44,380
Or did you even know her name?

40
00:03:45,890 --> 00:03:50,520
Did you tell Jang Yun because of Hong Yi Yeong, by any chance?

41
00:03:57,940 --> 00:03:59,870
Why is the reason important?

42
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:01,750
Because of her you wanted to break up with me.

43
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,250
It's not because of her, I told you.

44
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:08,160
If you don't love her, why are you by her side?

45
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,840
It's strange, isn't it?

46
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:16,360
I may not know anything else, but I know you don't love anyone, Conductor.

47
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,740
That's why it's even stranger.

48
00:04:19,990 --> 00:04:24,330
You were appointed to your post one year after Kim Ian's death, weren't you?

49
00:04:25,850 --> 00:04:28,840
That was the result of my achievements.

50
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:32,390
I know. How impressive.

51
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:36,030
I am really proud of you, Conductor.

52
00:04:36,030 --> 00:04:40,460
But even so, one year is a miracle.

53
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:44,740
Who brought you to this level?

54
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:47,050
In exchange for what?

55
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:51,150
Keep going.

56
00:04:51,150 --> 00:04:53,350
I really want to find out

57
00:04:53,350 --> 00:04:59,330
what you did to Hong Yi Yeong that night.

58
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:06,880
Because I want to see you fall to rock bottom.

59
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,890
And I'll be laughing when this happens.

60
00:05:18,310 --> 00:05:21,260
You shouldn't joke about things like this, Yi Yeong.

61
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:23,970
Do you think I would believe your promise?

62
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:28,740
If you find it, you could give it to someone else.

63
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,310
Do I look that stupid?

64
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:33,710
I won't give it to anyone else, I won't.

65
00:05:33,710 --> 00:05:37,540
I don't know what you're looking for, and I have no interest in it at all.

66
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:41,800
But Ahjussi, if you find it, you will get money for it, won't you?

67
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,950
So I will help you get that money.

68
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:46,320
Even if it is evidence of a murder?

69
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:48,750
Even if all sorts of dirty things are in there?

70
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:53,620
Do you think you can give that to me and live a good life, as if nothing happened?

71
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:58,080
You happened to stab someone by accident, and you live crying and whining about it all day long.

72
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:01,380
Can you? Can you?!?

73
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,010
I can do it.

74
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:09,610
I can do it, I'm telling you.

75
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:15,560
Ahjussi, just like you said, I even stabbed someone.

76
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:17,980
Please just leave our house.

77
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:20,850
For that, I could do anything.

78
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:27,020
Your heart is so admirable for thinking about your family.

79
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,930
But I don't trust anyone, not even a little bit.

80
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:35,730
There are repulsive people who will lie even at the moment they are being hung.

81
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:47,600
One year ago, on that night, in that warehouse,

82
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:50,160
there was someone else.

83
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,690
Someone else?

84
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:57,730
Not just me and Kim Ian, but someone else... ?

85
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,680
Who is it?

86
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,530
Please don't come closer.

87
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:06,210
Hey!

88
00:07:06,210 --> 00:07:09,750
Who are you? Who are you? Who?

89
00:07:09,750 --> 00:07:12,090
Think hard.

90
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:15,330
People don't always die after they get stabbed by a knife.

91
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:18,110
What does that mean?

92
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:25,160
Are you saying that maybe I didn't kill Kim Ian?

93
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:29,720
So who is that person?

94
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:33,420
You have to remember who that person was.

95
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:37,810
That person could be the real murderer.

96
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:43,860
Do you have a ballpoint pen distributed as a gift by the Sinyeong College of Music?

97
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:45,170
Ballpoint pen?

98
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:47,160
Find that and bring it to me.

99
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:54,210
Don't open it, don't try to find out, keep your mouth shut, and don't let anyone know.

100
00:07:54,210 --> 00:07:56,790
Then I will tell you.

101
00:07:56,790 --> 00:08:00,490
Who was there on that night, in that warehouse.

102
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,950
Be strong, Yi Yeong.

103
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:08,330
I'll give you my phone number.

104
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:35,350
Are you following me or something? I didn't know you were so interested in me.

105
00:08:36,530 --> 00:08:40,380
I'm disappointed. I enjoyed your conducting.

106
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:46,880
What did you exchange for your appointment as conductor? Is that why you killed Ian?

107
00:08:50,310 --> 00:08:57,420
You seem to really want to make me into a murderer. Let me ask you one thing.

108
00:08:57,420 --> 00:09:01,060
Could you exchange your brother with anything else?

109
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:04,730
Of course, a question has to make sense in order to have an answer, right?

110
00:09:04,730 --> 00:09:10,720
For me, my work is as important as Kim Ian is to you.

111
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:13,360
Fine, let's say that I'm here in exchange for something.

112
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:16,290
If I didn't have the right, or the skill, wouldn't that fact reveal itself?

113
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:18,400
Would people stand for it?

114
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:25,390
As soon as the performance is over, they would be after me, to fire me. So let's talk again after the performance.

115
00:09:32,330 --> 00:09:38,700
I Wanna Hear Your Song

116
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:43,600
CEO Jang, please take a lot of interest in us.

117
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,290
The orchestra members are extremely talented.

118
00:09:46,290 --> 00:09:49,400
They are full of artistic fervor.

119
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:03,670
How long have you known CEO Jang?

120
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:07,710
Since you fired me, Professor.

121
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,580
Is this an ordinary neigborhood?

122
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:18,950
As soon as the rumors died down, I would have summoned you again. But you couldn't wait, so you stabbed me in the back?

123
00:10:18,950 --> 00:10:21,740
Think about how I've taken care of you so far.

124
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:24,990
The end must be good for it to be good, Professor.

125
00:10:24,990 --> 00:10:28,760
Isn't that how everything is, in this world?

126
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:33,300
Professor, you don't seem to like CEO Jang very much.

127
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:37,320
CEO Jang is quite interested in you, though, Professor.

128
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:40,480
What kind of interest?

129
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:43,920
Just... in various ways.

130
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:51,560
By the way, is the secret school still in operation?

131
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:55,750
Thanks for everything, looking after someone like me.

132
00:10:58,230 --> 00:11:00,140
You...

133
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:06,150
Look at that.

134
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,340
Have a seat.

135
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:26,630
Have you committed a sin? Why can't you raise your head?

136
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:30,870
Auntie.

137
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:35,260
You don't have to say anything, I heard everything from Su Yeong.

138
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:38,480
Why didn't you tell us before?

139
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:41,390
How did you endure everything by yourself?

140
00:11:49,730 --> 00:11:51,590
Don't cry.

141
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:53,890
I've decided to not cry.

142
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:57,330
And I will forget about it.

143
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:04,430
This isn't avoiding it, but that you... that you'd do such a thing to someone...

144
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:10,030
I just can't imagine that you stabbed someone.

145
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:14,670
I raised you, and I know you.

146
00:12:17,220 --> 00:12:20,400
But I remember it, Auntie.

147
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,760
Your Unni told me this:

148
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:33,230
If someone has a big trauma, they can create scenes like that in their head.

149
00:12:33,230 --> 00:12:37,130
Yes, that could be true.

150
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:42,000
You are such a good girl, so you feel guilt.

151
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:52,210
It's alright.

152
00:12:53,610 --> 00:12:59,630
You can't go home from now on. Stay here for the time being.

153
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:05,350
I will tell Unni to sleep in the living room, alright?

154
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:19,070
Psychology

155
00:13:51,970 --> 00:13:58,050
Do you have a ballpoint pen distributed as a gift by the Sinyeong College of Music?

156
00:13:58,050 --> 00:13:59,350
Ballpoint pen?

157
00:13:59,350 --> 00:14:01,040
Find that and bring it to me.

158
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,050
Then I will tell you.

159
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:07,080
Who was there on that night, in that warehouse.

160
00:14:17,350 --> 00:14:20,390
I have to remember. I just have to.

161
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:28,280
If I hid something somewhere, where would that be?

162
00:14:39,730 --> 00:14:43,550
Maybe I don't have it...

163
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:53,950
Why are you standing there like that?

164
00:14:58,010 --> 00:15:00,190
What's that?

165
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:03,660
Have you been on the run for several days?

166
00:15:03,660 --> 00:15:05,700
Did you wait long for me?

167
00:15:08,130 --> 00:15:12,530
Turn on your cell phone, then you don't have to wait like this.

168
00:15:12,530 --> 00:15:15,370
You're just getting home?

169
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:19,310
I was so bored I thought I would go insane.

170
00:15:19,310 --> 00:15:21,130
Come in.

171
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,030
This is Ian's cell phone, you can look at it.

172
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:05,340
But why did you want to see it?

173
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:10,900
I wondered whether I might remember anything if I saw it.

174
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:15,000
I understand you for wanting to do something, anything. But you don't have to make such effort.

175
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,950
Look through it comfortably.

176
00:16:32,940 --> 00:16:34,260
Are you hungry?

177
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:36,140
Want some toast?

178
00:16:36,140 --> 00:16:38,730
No, it's alright.

179
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:02,900
Do you have a ballpoint pen distributed as a gift by the Sinyeong College of Music?

180
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:22,870
I heated it up.

181
00:17:22,870 --> 00:17:26,340
Seeing your face, I thought you should have a warm drink.

182
00:17:27,510 --> 00:17:30,010
Something happened today, didn't it?

183
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:36,090
It's alright, so tell me.

184
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:39,340
To be honest...

185
00:17:42,020 --> 00:17:44,630
I met Ahjussi, the one I saw in that warehouse.

186
00:17:44,630 --> 00:17:45,830
Where?

187
00:17:45,830 --> 00:17:47,420
At my uncle and aunt's shop.

188
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:50,210
He was working part-time there.

189
00:17:50,210 --> 00:17:55,230
He has a scar on his hand, and as soon as I saw it, suddenly,

190
00:17:55,230 --> 00:17:58,290
I remembered that night.

191
00:17:58,290 --> 00:18:03,550
He was the ahjussi who chased me that night.

192
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:05,280
My family members don't know about it.

193
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:08,180
I didn't tell them, I thought I might put them in danger.

194
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:11,740
What did he say?

195
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:24,290
He said if I don't make him mad, nothing will happen.

196
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:30,430
I think you should be with your family instead of alone.

197
00:18:30,430 --> 00:18:32,930
Get up, I will take you to your family's home.

198
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,750
What?

199
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:44,990
No, nothing.

200
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:46,710
Let's go.

201
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:06,110
Find that and bring it to me.

202
00:19:06,110 --> 00:19:10,710
Don't open it, don't try to find out, keep your mouth shut,

203
00:19:10,710 --> 00:19:13,030
and don't let anyone know.

204
00:19:13,030 --> 00:19:14,970
Then I will tell you.

205
00:19:14,970 --> 00:19:18,980
Who was there on that night, in that warehouse.

206
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:31,110
What's up, all of a sudden?

207
00:19:31,940 --> 00:19:36,750
What exactly is the item that you're looking for? How much does it cost?

208
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:39,910
If I tell you, will give it to me?

209
00:19:41,670 --> 00:19:43,950
Don't appear in front of Hong Yi Yeong.

210
00:19:43,950 --> 00:19:47,520
Don't ever come near anyone in her family.

211
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:51,470
So tell me, what that is, and how much it costs.

212
00:19:51,470 --> 00:19:55,220
You don't need to know what it is.

213
00:19:55,220 --> 00:20:00,030
The price? About 3 billion won  (about $2.5 million)?

214
00:20:04,050 --> 00:20:08,260
Say an amount that I can actually give and you can actually receive.

215
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:14,380
You're right, that amount of money is too much for someone like me.

216
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:23,220
Shall I say a briefcase chock-full of 500,000 won certificates?

217
00:20:23,220 --> 00:20:27,160
It's too heavy.  Too heavy.

218
00:20:29,140 --> 00:20:30,940
Your cell phone.

219
00:20:43,220 --> 00:20:47,530
Do you know anything about Sinyeong Philharmonic's conductor Nam Ju Wan?

220
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:51,930
How would I know anything about fancy people like the Conductor?

221
00:20:54,030 --> 00:20:57,420
My phone is a temporary phone, so my phone number can change.

222
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:59,460
If it changes, I will let you know.

223
00:20:59,460 --> 00:21:04,180
If you have the money, let me know. I will exchange it for the item.

224
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:52,780
Tomorrow is the performance. Do you have time to wander around like this?

225
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:55,870
I will take care of that.

226
00:21:55,870 --> 00:21:58,560
Please lend me some money, I will pay it back.

227
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:01,320
How will you spend it?

228
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,700
I just need some.

229
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:07,930
Just... ?

230
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:09,590
Yes.

231
00:22:13,020 --> 00:22:17,690
Think about the things you've said to me in the past.

232
00:22:17,690 --> 00:22:21,430
Last year, do you remember what you did to me when you left home?

233
00:22:21,430 --> 00:22:24,760
You said you don't even consider me your father.

234
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:29,100
So why should I have to give you money, without even knowing the reason?

235
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:33,010
Explain that to me, so that I can understand it.

236
00:22:36,650 --> 00:22:40,120
Are you shamelessly asking me for money

237
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:44,400
without telling me the reason, when you don't even consider me to be your father?

238
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:46,700
I'm begging you for it.

239
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:55,610
I beg you. I will pay you back in one month.

240
00:22:55,610 --> 00:22:58,680
Father, I never asked you for anything before.

241
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:00,920
And I won't ask again.

242
00:23:02,610 --> 00:23:08,680
Is this also related to the Ian incident?

243
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:15,220
If so, I refuse. I don't like you being involved in that.

244
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:16,610
It makes me tremble with fury.

245
00:23:16,610 --> 00:23:22,200
If you need my money, quit Sinyeong Philharmonic and leave this place,  as soon as tomorrow.

246
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,320
Then I will give it to you.

247
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:40,930
Grandmother.

248
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:44,610
Grandmother!

249
00:23:44,610 --> 00:23:47,560
Aigoo, hey, hey.

250
00:23:48,290 --> 00:23:49,870
Why are you clinging to me?

251
00:23:49,870 --> 00:23:51,730
You like it, come on.

252
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:53,270
Give that to me. Whoa.

253
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:55,350
Why is this so heavy? What is it?

254
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:58,220
What do you think? Side dishes.

255
00:23:58,220 --> 00:24:02,850
Ju Wan, this boy, he looks like a Seoul man, but his palate is all Ms. Bok Bun.

256
00:24:02,850 --> 00:24:04,170
Give that to me.

257
00:24:04,170 --> 00:24:05,280
I'm strong.

258
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:06,350
Oh, just give it to me.

259
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:08,780
- Let's go.
- Oh, okay.

260
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:12,960
Why I put this horse's head here?

261
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:17,430
This is Mendelssohn, who won twice at the Kentucky Derby.

262
00:24:17,430 --> 00:24:19,280
Of course you know Mendelssohn's "Spring Song."

263
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:21,270
And I, like this horse,

264
00:24:21,270 --> 00:24:24,190
will only look ahead, like tunnel vision, and run.

265
00:24:24,190 --> 00:24:28,420
With the sentiment that I will not lose focus...

266
00:24:33,580 --> 00:24:36,100
CEO Jang has arrived.

267
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:40,830
Everyone is here already.

268
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:42,950
I am a bit late.

269
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:45,750
It's nice to see you everyday, CEO Jang.

270
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:49,620
You're not going to talk about anything serious, are you?

271
00:24:49,620 --> 00:24:51,670
No.

272
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:58,400
What did you say just now?

273
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,750
Why would you talk about the conductor at this point in time?

274
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:06,690
Tomorrow is his inaugural concert. As soon as he is inaugurated, you want us to fire him?

275
00:25:06,690 --> 00:25:07,820
So that we become a laughing-stock?

276
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:11,730
There is no need to be so sensitive about this.

277
00:25:11,730 --> 00:25:16,500
But to be entrusted with the historic 20th anniversary concert of Sinyeong Philharmonic,

278
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:22,300
I think he lacks weight. I'm just sharing my thoughts.

279
00:25:34,060 --> 00:25:36,160
So he gave some money, is that all?

280
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:38,950
We are still an orchestra with 20 years of history.

281
00:25:38,950 --> 00:25:42,020
He only joined a few days ago, who is he to tell us to fire the conductor?

282
00:25:42,020 --> 00:25:46,290
He didn't tell us to fire him. Just that he lacks weight.

283
00:25:46,290 --> 00:25:49,960
But that's what he's saying. I told you that he would be a problem.

284
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:54,110
His son will definitely be a problem during the audit, how will we deal with that?

285
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:57,870
You know nowadays a hiring scandal is brutal.

286
00:25:58,530 --> 00:26:01,960
If you don't create a problem, Professor Kang, there will be no problem.

287
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:05,850
Why do you keep getting involved in this? The university isn't enough for you?

288
00:26:05,850 --> 00:26:08,450
Embezzling from the music school isn't enough?

289
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:11,980
Embezzling? Look here, Sister-in-law.

290
00:26:11,980 --> 00:26:14,840
Do you really have the right to say that to me now?

291
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:16,980
It's thanks to me that this place is thriving.

292
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:20,730
Professor Kang, please don't call me Sister-in-law just anywhere.

293
00:26:20,730 --> 00:26:22,950
I am the Chairwoman of the Board here.

294
00:26:22,950 --> 00:26:26,750
And about whom we should thank for making this place thrive, let me ask my father.

295
00:26:26,750 --> 00:26:29,320
Please stop butting in.

296
00:26:45,850 --> 00:26:48,130
What is Professor Kang's problem with CEO Jang, anyway?

297
00:26:48,130 --> 00:26:52,260
Why does he have his knives out? Do you know anything?

298
00:26:52,260 --> 00:26:54,060
Today, it must be because of Maestro Nam.

299
00:26:54,060 --> 00:26:56,820
They have known each other since college.

300
00:26:56,820 --> 00:27:00,430
And he has pride in his discovery of Maestro Nam.

301
00:27:02,370 --> 00:27:04,960
Why did CEO Jang bring up Nam Ju Wan, anyway?

302
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:09,230
Does he not like him? I just can't figure this out.

303
00:27:09,230 --> 00:27:15,050
Just in case, find some reason to fire Nam Ju Wan.

304
00:27:15,050 --> 00:27:19,930
If we must fire him, we can't just do it, we will need a reason.

305
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:22,350
Yes.

306
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:30,710
Conductor, Grandmother said she can't sleep at your home.

307
00:27:30,710 --> 00:27:33,270
She says your home is too fancy.

308
00:27:33,270 --> 00:27:34,180
So?

309
00:27:34,180 --> 00:27:37,550
I'm taking her to my home.

310
00:27:37,550 --> 00:27:41,470
No, not my Auntie's. The place where I live by myself. She can sleep in my room.

311
00:27:41,470 --> 00:27:43,780
Alright. I'll go there after I'm done here.

312
00:27:43,780 --> 00:27:45,640
Yes.

313
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:58,410
Professor Kang

314
00:28:20,130 --> 00:28:22,770
What brings you here?

315
00:28:22,770 --> 00:28:27,300
CEO Jang was just here. I just finished meeting with him.

316
00:28:27,300 --> 00:28:32,090
I'm apprehensive. I think he knows something and is making a move.

317
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:38,010
I don't know if he knows or if he just suspects, but he's making an issue out of you.

318
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:40,260
Me?

319
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:43,460
If things go badly, you might have to take a break immediately after your inaugural concert.

320
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:46,330
It's hard to know for sure, so mentally prepare yourself.

321
00:28:46,330 --> 00:28:50,330
Take a break? Are you saying you will fire me?

322
00:28:50,330 --> 00:28:52,390
What did I do wrong that I have to leave?

323
00:28:52,390 --> 00:28:54,470
Who said you did anything wrong?

324
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:57,380
It's thanks to you that Sinyeong Philharmonic is surviving, and anyone who needs to know that does know it.

325
00:28:57,380 --> 00:28:59,680
So why? How can they fire me?

326
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:03,350
They can always fabricate a reason. If you're fired, then you're fired. Is there always a reason?

327
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:04,630
You have to prevent it, Professor.

328
00:29:04,630 --> 00:29:09,340
Of course I will try my best, but I'm just telling you that things can go wrong.

329
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:20,250
Do you think everything will be over if I just quit?

330
00:29:20,250 --> 00:29:23,900
If that guy knows something, his next target will be you.

331
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:25,650
And do you think I will stay quiet if I get fired from here?

332
00:29:25,650 --> 00:29:29,330
No, I will never go down alone.

333
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:34,380
Are you finished?

334
00:29:36,220 --> 00:29:40,880
Are you looking for Hong Yi Yeong's item?

335
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:45,840
Or did you perhaps already find it?

336
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:50,010
You're not naively thinking that it is all I need to find and get rid of, are you?

337
00:29:50,010 --> 00:29:52,930
That has no meaning.

338
00:29:52,930 --> 00:29:56,760
Kim Ian died over an item that has no meaning at all.

339
00:29:56,760 --> 00:30:01,660
Think about it, I know everything bad that you did.

340
00:30:01,660 --> 00:30:05,380
If you want to cover that up, you will have to kill me.

341
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:07,980
Perhaps you are thinking of killing me, too?

342
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:14,850
Why would I kill people uselessly?

343
00:30:14,850 --> 00:30:17,330
Everything happened because of you.

344
00:30:17,330 --> 00:30:18,860
Kim Ian died because of you.

345
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:21,350
If only you didn't give Hong Yi Yeong that knife that day...

346
00:30:21,350 --> 00:30:23,030
Please stop.

347
00:30:23,030 --> 00:30:27,010
And Hong Yi Yeong's life became messed up because of you.

348
00:30:27,010 --> 00:30:29,450
You killed Kim Ian. You are his murderer. Got it?

349
00:30:29,450 --> 00:30:31,350
Please stop!

350
00:30:31,350 --> 00:30:34,180
Before all my patience disappears.

351
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:01,390
Did you kill Ian, Conductor?

352
00:31:01,390 --> 00:31:04,880
Do you really not remember this knife?

353
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:07,400
It's the knife that Ian was stabbed with.

354
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:10,510
Kim Ian died because of you.

355
00:31:10,510 --> 00:31:14,320
If only you didn't give Hong Yi Yeong that knife that day...

356
00:31:22,610 --> 00:31:24,620
Who are you?

357
00:31:24,620 --> 00:31:26,530
Who are you?

358
00:31:26,530 --> 00:31:30,060
Who are you to do this to us?

359
00:31:30,060 --> 00:31:31,360
Who are you, who are you?

360
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:33,800
Who are you?
